brightmare (0.36) unstable; urgency=low

  * Get rid of the brightmare-html executable.
    Use the --html option instead.
  * Make -h/--help print proper help message.
  * Shorten the --version output.
  * Improve documentation.
  * Improve the build system:
    + Fix build failure with OCaml 4.05.
    + Use ocamlopt (instead of ocamlopt.opt) and ocamldep (instead of
      ocamldep.opt).
    + Add install target to Makefile.
    + Stop shipping Makefile.dep (it's a generated file).
      Remove it in the clean target.
    + Disable network access for xsltproc.
  * Put license into a separate file.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Mon, 01 Jan 2018 14:16:22 +0100

brightmare (0.35) unstable; urgency=low

  * Change the license to the Expat license.
  * Improve error handling.
  * Improve the manual pages, as per man-pages(7) recommendations:
    + Remove the “AUTHOR” section.
    + Rename the “USAGE EXAMPLE” section as “EXAMPLE”.
    + Fix wording in a few places.
  * Remove some unused cruft from Makefile.
  * Remove Debian packaging.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Thu, 31 Jan 2013 21:23:42 +0100

brightmare (0.34.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix a syntax error, which appears with current OCaml compiler.
  * Provide manual pages.
  * Add support for \newline.

